tio \${\textbackslash}sim2\$ orders of magnitude above the local relation, but consistent with other high-\$z\$ AGN discovered by JWST. The source is unresolved in all bands, implying a very compact size \${\textbackslash}lesssim200\$ pc in the UV. This suggests that the simultaneous buildup of compact stellar populations (i.e., galaxy bulges) and the central SMBH is ongoing even at \$z{$>$}7\$.},
